Three persons, who were kidnapped by some gunmen in Ayobo Housing Scheme Extension, Oshin in Ayobo-Ipaja, Lagos State, have been released. The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports that the victims: two sisters and a man were abducted on Friday and Sunday respectively by gunmen who invaded their estate. NAN reports that the parents of the two sisters, Mr Rashidi and Mrs Oluwalogbon Salami, were grateful to God for the safe return of their daughters.   Three shot dead, homes razed in Plateau attack     BEDC’s disputed debt suit adjourned till May 30     Seven die, houses burnt in Jigawa, Rivers fire   Mrs Oluwalogbon Salami told NAN yesterday that the entire family was happy because not all that were kidnapped usually returned. “We are very grateful to God for the victory He has given to our family; to God alone be the glory.” she said. Police spokesman Benjamin Hundeyin confirmed that the release of the three persons. It was learnt that the gunmen came through the boundary between Lagos and Ogun, and escaped with their victims on a speedboat.